<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06245138 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06245138 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  HOCKEY; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Team USA didn't need a pep talk or motivational speech, nor did it want one.All it needed for inspiration in its Canada Cup opener against Sweden onSaturday was the knowledge that a coach battling for his life drew up the gameplan.;   The United States, relying on strategy designed hours before byseriously ill Coach Bob Johnson, got its first two goals from Jeremy Roenickwithin a span of 2 minutes, 8 seconds in the first period and defeated worldchampion Sweden 6-3.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JOHNSON MAPS STRATEGY FOR U.S. WIN OVER SWEDEN  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Just a day after undergoing emergency surgery to remove a life-threateningbrain tumor, Johnson, coach of the Stanley Cup champion Pittsburgh Penguins,chose the U.S. lineup and outlined strategy to combat world champion Sweden'sphysical fore-checking.;   Johnson, partially paralyzed and unable to speech,sketched the plans and slipped them to Team USA co-General Manager CraigPatrick on Saturday morning.;   &quot;His mind's as sharp as ever,&quot; Patrick said.;  &quot;He was on everybody's minds,&quot; said Tim Taylor, who coached in Johnson'sabsence. &quot;Here's a man in the hospital, battling for his life, and he'sworried about beating Sweden. I didn't mention it, but it was on everybody'sminds. I knew it would affect us and strengthen our resolve. And I'm glad wewon.&quot;;   The U.S. team built a 5-0 lead midway through the second period, thensurvived three third-period goals by Sweden.; ETC.: NHL scoring champion BrettHull left the ice with a sprained left knee midway in the third period anddidn't return. He said the injury wasn't serious. . . . Czechoslovakia beatthe Soviet Union 5-2. Defending champion Canada met Finland in Toronto laterSaturday in another round-robin game.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Pittsburgh  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910901  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  283  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, September 1, 199100245138,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>